<taxonomicName box="[563,621,873,896]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Pigritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gruis">
<emphasis box="[563,621,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">gruis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[913,962,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">grus</emphasis>
meaning, a crane.
</paragraph>
